7. coheredem . . . scrip-it. It be- came a common practice under bad emperors thus to sacrifice a part of the property to save the rest for the rela- tives. Gaius exacted this (Suet. Cal. 38), and some famous instanoes are given under Nero in which this was done or recommended to be done (A. 14. 31, 13 16. 11, 2).
